From a03b1935ba3497e84fc3efee5b5e895c4716016b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 08:19:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Extract shared stylesheet, refactor page templates, and add
 project pages

### Motivation
- Consolidate duplicated inline styles into a single shared stylesheet to simplify maintenance and ensure consistent styling across pages.
- Improve markup structure and accessibility for the site navigation and logo.
- Add placeholder project pages to provide navigation targets for programming and screenwriting sections.

### Description
- Extracted all repeated CSS into a new file `assets/style.css` and replaced inline `<style>` blocks in `index.html`, `about.html`, and `404.html` with a single `<link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/style.css">`.
- Unified page structure by applying `main` class names (`card`, `card--wide`) and renaming navigation/footer elements to `nav.site-nav` and `footer.site-footer`, plus updated positioning classes (`logo-wrap`, `hero-line`, `error-title`, `error-sub`, `about-section`, etc.).
- Replaced bare `<img>` logo usage with a `<picture>` that prefers the SVG (`assets/scbutterfly...svg`) and falls back to PNG for better fidelity and progressive enhancement.
- Added new navigation links and accessibility attributes such as `aria-label="Primary navigation"` and `aria-current="page"` on active links, and created two new pages: `programming-projects.html` and `screenwriting-projects.html` with a shared layout and "Coming Soon" placeholders.

### Testing
- No automated tests were run for this change.
